@NODE LIMIT "Public Domain Version Limitations."

	The main limitation of the Public Domain Version is that the Maximum Number of
disks that can be logged is 25 per database, (of which only two of six are available)
If you wish to keep a catalogue of more than 25 disks, using all the databases, then please
order the @{" REGISTERED " LINK CORR} Version, which is not disabled in any way.
@ENDNODE

@NODE QU "What does the program do?"


	If you are reading this it may be that you are just curious or that you have a
disk/program storage problem. Well TurboCAT-Pro is designed to solve some of your problems.
Have a look a the@{" History " LINK HISTORY} part of the document to get an idea how it all
began.

	Overview:

	TurboCAT-Pro is used to compile and edit a complete record of what disks you have
and, probably more importantly, what is on them. It is probably unique in that the database for
all the disks stored by the program is held in memory while the program is running. This means
that you can obtain data about your collection without having to wait for what seems like hours 
using other programs while the data is accessed from individual data files.

	This program has many features which are accessable from the main screen. Most importantly
After compiling and saving your database(s) you may wish to search for a particular file. This can 
be done by clicking on the 'Search' button, which takes you to the 'Search' screen. At the top 
right hand corner of the window is a field into which you may type in the name of the program or 
file that you are looking for. If it is in the root directory or one level below root, of any of 
the disks which you have catalogued using TurboCAT-Pro, then the search routine will find it, 
tell you which disk it is on, and offer you the the option of viewing the entire contents of 
that disk. You may then print any results that you obtain. 

	After performing a search, if any matches have been found, you may view the disk contents
by double-clicking on the 'match' that you are interested in. The contents will be displayed in
the lower viewport.

	The program saves me time regularly....I hope you find it as handy as I do!
@ENDNODE
