@NODE HISTORY "A short history of the programs"

   "ow did it come about then?"

   I had started to build up quite a collection of programs and used to get really annoyed when
it took me half an hour just to find the one that I had been looking for, when, by that time, 
I usually had lost the thread with what I had been doing. So I tried to get hold of a disk 
cataloguing program, I tried a couple which either looked naff, didn't do what I wanted, or
simply took an age to search my collection. So I used my coverdisk, (Thanks AC), and had a go 
myself. The program started off quite simply but began to sprout arms and legs and then slowly 
became the monster it is now. As it is it does just what I wanted, I have all my disks catalogued 
using Turbocat-Pro and use 'Search' to find the file that I want, the search time can be less than 
15 seconds including loading time.....a long way from half an hour.

   Any way, I do hope you find the program as useful as I do, all suggestions for improvement are
 gratefully received....

        ... David

@{" ** Version History ** " LINK VERSION}
@ENDNODE



