@NODE INSTALL "Installation to Hard Drive"


   TurboCat And TurboView work perfectly well from floppy, but load a lot faster when run from a
hard drive.

	There is an installer program on the disk for you to use, it has been written using
Commododore's, (Or is it Escoms'?), installer program. To use the installer, boot from your Hard
Drive as usual then run the install program, The process takes about 2-3 minutes. I have not
forced the installer to add an assign to your SYS:S/User-Startup because I find that many people
have their startup files write protected, which may have caused a problem with the installer. 
	This is something that you need to do yourself, luckily it is very easy to do:


Here's what to do:-

   1) Boot from your normal boot partition. (Very Important!)

   2) Run the "Install_TurboCAT-Pro" program and note the full path that the program has been
	installed to, ie 'WORK:PROGRAMS/TURBOCAT-PRO' or 'WORK:TURBOCAT-PRO'

   3) Using the shell, type ED S:USER-STARTUP, move the cursor to the end of this file and onto a
      newline and type ASSIGN TURBOCAT-PRO: 'your-path-as-described above:', (remember the colons!). 
      Save the file and exit the editor. Reboot your machine. You should find that the program
      runs fine. 
   
   4) Thats it, if you have any problems, please re-read the above to make sure you have not made a
      small mistake. If you still have a problem, then I am sorry, write to me with your setup and I
      will try to help you. 

** Please note 1:

	the installer will automatically create a drawer called TurboCAT-Pro at your chosen 
	destination, therefore if you use the 'create new drawer' option, and call it TurboCAT-Pro, 
	your assign path will need to be set something like:

	'Assign TurboCAT-Pro: Work:turbocat-pro/turbocat-pro' (drawer within drawer)

** Please note 2:

	After installation you will find that if you try to scan your original floppy
      	'TurboCAT-Pro' disk using a hard-drive resident program, then the system will re-point the 
      	assign to DF0:. The solution is,if you wish to scan the disk for your records, 
	to 'ReName' It!, ie TurboCAT-PRO(F) or something like that.

@ENDNODE



@NODE PHIL "How to use the program"

	Philosophical Truism: 

	"Men live lives of silent anguish".....(No really the program philosophy follows)

   How to make the best use of the program:-

   1) If you possibly can, install Turbocat-Pro to your hard drive, this makes it so much
      easier to update and search your Databases.

   2) Run the program, select a database and insert your entire collection of disks into drive DF0:, 
      (no, not all at once!), numbering each one with a large ink marker as you go. Save when you 
      have finished. 

   3) Once you have done this, use the search facility to seek the file you wish to find, after a short
      delay.....bobs your uncle, if it's there you will find it, The program will tell which disk it is 
      on and most importantly it's number with which you can find your disk, (assuming you also store 
      them in numeric order!!)

   4) If you have a pile of disks called 'empty' or something similar you may be pleased to know that
      you can change the volume name, (in the list not the disk), after it has been logged to
      something more meaningful like '24bit backdrops 1" or "Bassy sounds". Try it!

  5)  Remember if you are using the unregistered version of TurboCAT-Pro, it will only allow you to log
      a maximum of 25 disks per database (only 2 of 6 available) sorry about this, but I feel a 
      shareware fee of a Tenner is not too much to ask someone who intends to fully use the programs.
@ENDNODE
@NODE PRINT "Various print options"

	There are two places in TurboCAT where you may make use of the printer support:

	a) Main Screen:

	On the main screen, if you select 'Print', you will be taken to a window which will ask you
if you wish to print either the 'disklist' or the 'selected contents'.@(If no contents are presently
selected then the 'selected contents' option will be ghosted). When you select either option you 
will be told that the selected 'document' will have 'x' number of lines and be asked you if you wish
to proceed. If you do, just click on the 'yes' button and the document will be spooled to your
printer. If not, click on 'no', and you will be returned to the print options window.

	b) Search Screen:

	Should you wish to, it's possible to print out your recently compiled list of 'matches'. Use
the menu option "Print all Matches", or if you wish to print out the list of the disk contents, then
use the "Print Contents" option. (This interface has yet to be refined)

Should you wish to print either of these lists, use the print button. The print part of the program
operates via your preference settings, and your own printer driver may be used in the DEVS/Printers
drawer.


@ENDNODE
@NODE NOW "Scan Now! Information"

	Hitting This button will auto-scan whatever disk happens to be in drive DF0: or DF1:
 and adds it to the database. (Scanning mode must be on, though.)
@ENDNODE
@NODE NOTES "Other information"

	If you have a large disk collection, say greater than 300 disks, you will find that when you
save the database, there is some delay while this is carried out. This is because all the data is
re-sorted, copied to RAM:, crunched, then copied to volume TurboCAT-Pro:, please be patient during this.
	A progress indicator will tell you how things are going.
@ENDNODE
